<span class="header1">CREATIVE BUSINESS</span>
<p>You can be successful in this field if you have a talent and can manage business matters yourself. This field combines artistic talent with practical business sense.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Chef</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BC/43009.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Chef" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you became a chef, you would use your creativity to prepare new kinds of dishes or meals for others to eat. You would work in a kitchen creating new recipes, preparing the meals, and overseeing the staff.  Creativity is important to a chef.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>No college degree is needed.  Most chefs learn their craft at schools called "culinary institutes."  Chefs who do not train at a culinary institute are put through a tough on-the-job training program while working in a kitchen at another job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A yearly salary for a chef ranges from $19,000 to $75,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Illustrator</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BC/43312.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Illustrator" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Illustrators draw or paint pictures that go with somebody else's words.  Their goal is to "add to" the appeal or impact of the words.  Their work can be found in newspapers, magazines, books, and greeting cards.  It can be found in TV commercials as well.  As an illustrator, you would be most likely to find work with an advertising agency.  But other organizations hire illustrators too.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Most illustrators have had some post high school courses. A Bachelor's Degree from a college, university, or an art school is a definite advantage.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The salary of an illustrator ranges from $18,000 to $73,000+.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Interior Designer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BC/43032.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Interior Designer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you have a "knack" for making a room look its best, you might become an interior designer. Interior designers help their clients decorate the inside of homes, offices, and businesses.  In this job, you would decorate rooms working within a budget. To do this, you would have to know the best prices on furniture, drapes, and room accessories.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need to complete a three to four-year program in interior designing.  You must also be a member of a professional association to find a job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>An interior designer may make from $21,000 to $70,000 a year. The salary depends on the company and the designer's reputation.</blockquote>

